metadata.name: Coextending
metadata.description:
Rule #1  
Parallels can be defined as worlds that are developing parallel at equal distances from each other and never meet. 

About the collection:  
Every photo in the collection reveals geometric nature. One art - one rule of parallels. The architectural vision is decomposing reality into structural elements to see fundamental rules and directions.
